# Design Tokens ‚Äî use them or propose them

## Hard rule: no arbitrary values

In any file outside `packages/ui/src/components/primitives/`:

- **No raw hex** (`#abcdef`).
- **No raw `px`** literal in strings (`"16px"`, `padding: "12px"`).
- **No `rgb()` / `rgba()` / `hsl()` / `hsla()`** literals.
- **No inline `style={}`** on JSX.
- **No Tailwind default palette** colors in new code: `bg-gray-*`,
  `text-red-*`, `border-gray-*`, `bg-blue-*`, etc. Use semantic tokens.
- **No arbitrary Tailwind values** like `text-[14px]`, `bg-[#2E5BFF]`,
  `p-[18px]`. If a value doesn't exist as a token, add the token.

ESLint catches the literal cases. The Tailwind cases are caught in
review ‚Äî and now, by you.

## Token sources

- **Source of truth:** `packages/ui/src/tokens/tokens.json`.
- **Generated CSS variables:** `packages/ui/src/tokens/tokens.css` ‚Äî do
  not edit.
- **Generated TS const:** `packages/ui/src/tokens/tokens.ts` ‚Äî do not
  edit.
- **Tailwind theme:** `packages/ui/tailwind.config.ts` ‚Äî surfaces tokens
  as utilities.
- **Generator:** `scripts/generate-tokens.mjs` (`npm run tokens:generate`,
  CI: `npm run tokens:check`).

## What to use, by need

Pick the token whose **intent** matches yours. Don't pick by visual
match ‚Äî pick by purpose.

### Color

| Need | Token | Tailwind |
|------|-------|----------|
| Page background | `surface.default` | `bg-surface` |
| Card / sheet background | `surface.raised` | `bg-surface-raised` |
| Inset zone (list striping, sidebar) | `surface.sunken` | `bg-surface-sunken` |
| Modal scrim | `surface.overlay` | `bg-surface-overlay` |
| Body / heading text | `text.primary` | `text-text-primary` |
| Labels, secondary headings | `text.secondary` | `text-text-secondary` |
| Hints, captions, timestamps | `text.muted` | `text-text-muted` |
| Text on inverted surface | `text.inverse` | `text-text-inverse` |
| Text on accent-filled element | `text.onAccent` | `text-text-onAccent` |
| Primary action / link | `accent.default` | `bg-accent`, `text-accent` |
| Hover of accent | `accent.hover` | `hover:bg-accent-hover` |
| Accent-tinted background | `accent.subtle` | `bg-accent-subtle` |
| Success (set done, payment) | `signal.success` | `bg-signal-success`, `text-signal-success` |
| Error / destructive | `signal.danger` | `bg-signal-danger`, `text-signal-danger` |
| Soft warning | `signal.warning` | `bg-signal-warning`, `text-signal-warning` |
| **Personal record only** | `signal.pr` | `bg-signal-pr`, `text-signal-pr` |
| Hairline / card divider | `border.subtle` | `border-border-subtle` |
| Default form border | `border.default` | `border-border` |
| High-emphasis divider | `border.strong` | `border-border-strong` |
| Focus ring | `--color-focus-ring` | `ring` (default ring color) |

### Spacing ‚Äî pick by intent

Three axes; pick by **direction and purpose**, not just size:

| Token | Direction | Use |
|-------|-----------|-----|
| `space.inset.{xs,sm,md,lg,xl}` | inward (padding) | Padding inside containers (`p-inset-md`). |
| `space.stack.{xs,sm,md,lg,xl}` | vertical (gap/margin) | Gap between stacked elements (`gap-stack-md`). |
| `space.inline.{xs,sm,md,lg}` | horizontal (gap/margin) | Gap between inline elements (`gap-inline-sm`). |

### Radius

- `rounded-control` ‚Äî buttons, inputs, badges.
- `rounded-card` ‚Äî cards, sheets, panels.
- `rounded-pill` ‚Äî pills, avatars, fully-rounded tags.

### Shadow

- `shadow-sm` ‚Äî subtle elevation (card hairline).
- `shadow` ‚Äî default elevation (raised card).
- `shadow-lg` ‚Äî modal, popover.
- `shadow-focus` ‚Äî focus ring shadow (used by primitives).

### Motion

- Duration: `duration-fast` (120ms) / `base` (200ms) / `slow` (320ms).
- Easing: `ease-standard` (decelerate) / `ease-emphasized` (signature
  moments only ‚Äî PR, completion).

### Typography

- Family: `font-sans` (default) / `font-mono` (numbers in code-y
  contexts).
- Sizes: use the Tailwind type scale (`text-xs ‚Ä¶ text-3xl`). Body text
  is **16px minimum** (`text-base`). Never use `text-sm` for body copy
  on mobile.
- **Tabular numbers** for any column of numbers: `tabular-nums`.

## Adding a token

1. Add to `packages/ui/src/tokens/tokens.json` under the right layer
   (`primitive.*`, `semantic.{light,dark}.*`, etc.).
2. Run `npm run tokens:generate`.
3. Surface it in `packages/ui/tailwind.config.ts` if it should be a
   utility.
4. Document it in `design-system/tokens/README.md`.
5. Record in `design-system/changelog.md` under `[Unreleased]`.
6. Mention the new token in your `Design-system decisions:` reply.

## Bad ‚Üí good examples

```tsx
// ‚ùå Raw hex + raw px + inline style
<div style={{ backgroundColor: "#2E5BFF", padding: "16px" }}>‚Ä¶</div>

// ‚úÖ Semantic tokens via Tailwind utilities
<div className="bg-accent p-inset-md">‚Ä¶</div>

// ‚ùå Tailwind default palette
<button className="bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white">‚Ä¶</button>

// ‚úÖ Reuse the primitive ‚Äî variants already encode this
import { Button } from "@famm/ui";
<Button>Save changes</Button>

// ‚ùå Arbitrary Tailwind value
<p className="text-[15px] leading-[22px]">‚Ä¶</p>

// ‚úÖ Use the scale. If the scale lacks what you need, add a token.
<p className="text-base leading-relaxed">‚Ä¶</p>
```

## After editing ‚Äî explain

In `Design-system decisions:`:

- Tokens used: `bg-surface-raised`, `text-text-muted`, `gap-stack-md`.
- New token? Note it: e.g. "added `signal.streak` to `tokens.json` ‚Äî
  see changelog entry. **Regenerated tokens** with
  `npm run tokens:generate`."
- `OPEN:` if a value didn't fit any existing token and you couldn't
  decide whether to add one.
